    "actor_description": "I push and the world doesn't move. The same wall, every time. Heat climbs my neck; my hands clench like they're trying to become tools. I can feel my mind searching for leverage-anything to grab-and coming back empty. The worst part is the wasted energy: all this drive, nowhere it can actually go.",
    "description_text": "{actor} paces in place without getting anywhere-fists tightening, jaw working, breath coming sharp. They look for exits, options, handles that aren't there. The anger shows, but it keeps folding back on itself, trapped.",
